{"questionId":"22210163","questionHtml":"<p>Given that the series expansion for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup></math> is convergent for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>1</mn></math>, state the restriction which must be placed on <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> for the approximation&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup><mo>≈</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>19</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;to be valid.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>&lt;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22210163","referenceCode":"24M.1.AHL.TZ2.12d","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Given that the series expansion for 1-ax-12 is convergent for ax<1, state the restriction which must be placed on x for the approximation 1-2x-121-4x-12≈2+6x+19x22 to be valid.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.19—Maclaurin series"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}